Lecture (Week 11a): Density Estimation

1. Data

data(faithful)
head(faithful)
  eruptions waiting
1     3.600      79
2     1.800      54
3     3.333      74
4     2.283      62
5     4.533      85
6     2.883      55
attach(faithful)
plot(eruptions, waiting)

hist(eruptions, freq=FALSE, breaks=50)                # histogram as density

2. KDE

par(mfrow=c(2,2))
for(bw in c(0.03, 0.07, 0.1, 0.3)) {
   hist(eruptions, freq=FALSE, breaks=40, 
        col="gray80", border="white",
        main=paste0("h = ", bw), xlab="Eruption Time")
   lines(density(eruptions, bw=bw), col=4, lwd=2)
}

Several bandwidth selection methods:

par(mfrow=c(2,2))
for(bw in c("nrd0", "ucv", "bcv", "SJ")) {
   hist(eruptions, freq=FALSE, breaks=40, 
        col="gray80", border="white",
        main=paste0("h = ", bw), xlab="Eruption Time")
   lines(density(eruptions, bw=bw), col=4, lwd=2)
}

3. Univariate Mixtures

library(mclust)
Package 'mclust' version 5.4.7
Type 'citation("mclust")' for citing this R package in publications.
(r = densityMclust(eruptions, G=2, modelNames="E"))   # 2 components, equal variance
'densityMclust' model object: (E,2)

plot(r, eruptions, "density", breaks=50, lwd=2, col=4)
